-- python install mac
download latest python
right click pkg file to start Python Installer, follow the instruction
phthon will be installed in Applications directory, /Applications/Python 3.9
double click Install Certification icon in the Finder window to install certification (required)
type python to verify version
$ python --version
PATH=/bin:/usr/bin:/usr/local/bin:${PATH}
export PATH

-- venv
- cd to my directory and create venv
$ python3 -m venv tutorial-env
active venv
$ source tutorial-env/bin/activate
run your version
$ pathon
>>> import sys
>>> sys.path

-- pip installation (already included in python)
$ python -m pip --version (pip 20.2.3 from /Users/..)
$ pip list (list all packages installed)
$ (tutorial-env) $ pip freeze > requirements.txt
$ (tutorial-env) $ cat requirements.txt
$ python -m pip install -r requirements.txt (install required packages when release)

-- install django
$ python -m django --version (3.1.5, check current version)
$ python -m pip install Django (install if need)
$ python
>>> import django
>>> print(django.get_version()) (verify version is 3.1.5)

-- create django project
$ django-admin startproject mysite
mysite/
    manage.py (command-line utility)
    mysite/
        __init__.py (Python package indicator)
        settings.py (Django config)
        urls.py (Django project url)
        asgi.py (ASGI-compatible web servers)
        wsgi.py (WSGI-compatible web servers)
        
        
        


